comments: don\'t let him scare you away from this class. it can start off overwhelming, but he\'s a good instructor. there 5 SHORT ANSWER quizzes (about 15% each) and the final, also short answers. a (long) list of questions will be given prior to the quiz, from which the quiz questions will be chosen. Extra credit opportunities through quizzes & experimetrix.

Really interesting professor, clear and easy to understand. Fair on tests, gives extra points. Definitely one of the classes I looked forward to most this quarter. Basically tells you all you need to go so just attend lecture.

This class is pretty easy if you go to lecture and pay attention. He tells you which pages you need to read in the book as well. If you read those pages and go to lectures I am sure you will get a good grade. He\'s awkward at times but he is a nice guy and means well. :)
The prof makes the class really easy and interesting. Just go to lecture and listen and you will do well in the class. He really cares about everyone doing well and gives extra credit opportunities.

Professor Kennelly is one of the best professors I\'ve had for my two yrs of college. Even though I\'m not a PSYC major, his class was pretty easy! Just go to all his lectures, he makes them so entertaining you don\'t fall asleep or anything. He\'s a really nice guy and his TAs are super nice too! Tests are heavily lectured-based. I\'d take him again!!
really interesting class. fair tests and extra credit!

Prof. Kennelley\'s probably the best professor i\'ve ever gotten so far.His lectures are straightforward and test questions are based off of his powerpoint slideshow.If he didn\'t talk about it in class then it won\'t be on the test.I didn\'t get into the class till week 2, so i went to his office hour and he gave me a whole review on what i\'ve missed.

Kennelly is an awesome professor for this class. He explains the material very well and makes note-taking very easy (powerpoint). His tests are not that hard, but some questions might be tricky, but he offers bonus points. This class is interesting, but there is a lot of things you need to memorize.
You don\'t really need the textbook, everything he tests us on is in lecture. He is a pretty funny guy and the class is easy.

He\'s definitely easier than other psyc professors. Anything in the textbook that is not discussed in lecture will not be tested, which reduces LOTS of studying time. On the 1st midterm, about 40-ish% of the class this quarter got A\'s and B\'s and the avg was 77%. The multiple choice can be tricky, so make sure you really understand the concepts.

Great teach, great guy. Very fun and personable. However, psych the 120 and 121 class is hard. I\'m talking about a quiz every other week about 60 questions long at the average that you half to memorize. However, he allows a retake every friday. I\'d rather have a great teacher and a hard class, then vice versa. I\'d say take him.

Looks and sounds like a young Nicholas Cage. Very entertaining professor, used South Park\'s characters as examples in class. Most of the material comes from notes, but in my case, reading the book helped. The exams are tricky, so don\'t wait until the last minute to study. Terms can get confusing after a while, but hey, it\'s behavioral psych.
Don\'t buy the textbook, but make sure to go to lecture. Tests are based off notes you take in lecture. Lectures are clear and semi-entertaining.
Prof Kennelly is great. He gives lots of examples and is really funny. Definitely take his class if you can! He\'s one of my favorite professors.
Awesome professor. Funny, clear, great. Best professor I\'ve had.
